2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
1 unit(s) Chickpeas
1 unit(s) Ciabatta Roll
1 unit(s) Carrot
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Baby Spinach
1 tsp Chili Flakes
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*

Peel, then coarsely grate carrot.
Core, then cut pepper into ½-inch pieces.
Halve ciabatta.

Heat a large pot over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties, peppers and carrots. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Add 2 tsp (4 tsp) Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend and ¼ tsp chili flakes. (NOTE: Reference heat guide.) Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min.

Add crushed tomatoes, chickpeas with their liquid, stock powder and 1/3 cup (1/2 cup) water. Bring to a boil over high.
Once boiling, reduce heat to medium and simmer, stirring occasionally, until stew thickens slightly, 7-8 min.
Add spinach. Season with salt and pepper, then stir until spinach wilts, 1 min. (TIP: If you prefer a more brothy stew, add more water, 1-2 tbsp at a time!)

Meanwhile, combine re maining Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil in a small bowl.
Add ciabatta to an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up. Brush oil mixture onto cut sides.
Toast in the middle of the oven, tossing halfway through, until golden, 5-6 min.

Divide stew between bowls.
Serve spiced toasts alongside for dipping.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the chorizo, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**